16:18.879 --> 16:20.879
♪ Came in that...with the mob ♪

16:20.881 --> 16:22.815
♪ Left out that...with ya... ♪

16:22.817 --> 16:24.416
♪ Get down low, hit licks ♪

16:24.418 --> 16:26.352
♪ Stack up the paper, get rich ♪

16:26.354 --> 16:27.820
♪ You better be lucky, I miss ♪

16:27.822 --> 16:30.022
♪ I'm tryna put pointers
in my wrist ♪

16:30.024 --> 16:32.358
Shiloh have time
for a quick one-on-one?

16:32.360 --> 16:34.493
You know he does.
Hey, yo, Shi.

16:34.495 --> 16:36.228
Come on, man, come on.
'Sup, man?

16:36.230 --> 16:38.497
Time to go to work, but don't go
anywhere, all right?

16:38.499 --> 16:39.966
I won't.
Stevie.

16:39.968 --> 16:42.300
Take care of my girl Danielle
over here, all right?

16:42.302 --> 16:44.770
Let's go.
Let's go, man.

16:44.772 --> 16:46.038
Hey, yo!

16:46.040 --> 16:47.640
♪ You never know
a...be plottin' ♪

16:47.642 --> 16:48.975
♪ Why you playin'?
I got the chop-- ♪

16:48.977 --> 16:50.442
[ Music stops ]

16:50.444 --> 16:53.712
[ Saw buzzing ]

16:53.714 --> 16:55.247
What's --
What's going on?

16:55.249 --> 16:56.448
Are they working
over here?

16:56.450 --> 16:58.017
Dude said he'd be quick.

16:59.988 --> 17:03.255
Gentlemen, I got to take care
of some business, all right?

17:03.257 --> 17:05.123
I'll be back.

17:05.125 --> 17:06.258
Come on, man.

17:06.260 --> 17:13.666
♪♪

17:13.668 --> 17:16.869
[ Cellphone vibrates ]

17:20.274 --> 17:21.473
Yo, someone's coming.

17:21.475 --> 17:23.342
I'll handle it.

17:26.146 --> 17:29.147
Hey, yo! Yo!

17:29.149 --> 17:30.549
Hey.

17:30.551 --> 17:32.484
What's going on here?

17:32.486 --> 17:34.152
Uh, we're just
doing some work.

17:34.154 --> 17:36.622
Yeah, no shit.
Why?

17:36.624 --> 17:39.091
Well, uh, the owner
had some punch-list,

17:39.093 --> 17:41.560
uh, stuff for us to do,
so we're just getting it done

17:41.562 --> 17:43.762
before we inspect --
Bullshit.

17:43.764 --> 17:46.032
I pay Warren not to work
on my demo days.

17:46.034 --> 17:48.500
Well, I don't know
what to tell you, man.

17:48.502 --> 17:50.603
I'm just doing j--
You don't know what to...

17:51.839 --> 17:53.906
All right, how about
I tell<i> you</i> something?

17:53.908 --> 17:55.774
How about
we call up Warren,

17:55.776 --> 17:57.243
I get your dumb ass
fired over the phone,

17:57.245 --> 18:00.079
and then I knock your teeth out
just to pass the time?

18:02.650 --> 18:04.182
We'll wrap up
and get out of your way.

18:04.184 --> 18:07.653
I'm sorry.
We don't want any trouble.

18:07.655 --> 18:09.521
Pack your shit up

18:09.523 --> 18:11.590
and get out of here.

18:11.592 --> 18:14.526
You got it.

18:14.528 --> 18:16.062
You got 10 minutes.

18:16.064 --> 18:19.665
♪♪

18:19.667 --> 18:20.867
What's going on?

18:20.869 --> 18:24.403
Hey, we gotta go.
The job's burned.

18:24.405 --> 18:25.604
What?

18:25.606 --> 18:26.805
They pay the owner
of this building

18:26.807 --> 18:28.006
not to work on demo days.

18:28.008 --> 18:30.809
We gotta go now.
God damn it.

18:30.811 --> 18:35.882
♪♪

18:35.884 --> 18:37.349
Hey, hey, Warren,
call me, man.

18:37.351 --> 18:40.352
There's people
working next door.

18:40.354 --> 18:41.820
W-We're already
through this wall.

18:41.822 --> 18:43.021
We're almost
to the safe.

18:43.023 --> 18:44.690
Yo, let's go!
He said we're burned!

18:44.692 --> 18:46.625
Job's not burned.
He just said we're burned.

18:46.627 --> 18:48.094
The job is not burned!

18:48.096 --> 18:49.695
We'll walk now, we strike
a new deal with Pamela

18:49.697 --> 18:51.230
when we get out!
No.

18:51.232 --> 18:53.699
This is for our house!

18:53.701 --> 18:55.568
It's for everything we've worked
for our entire lives!

18:55.570 --> 18:58.437
It's all in that wall!
Bro, this is jail,
and Renn is next door, bro!

18:58.439 --> 18:59.906
Renn is gonna be fine.

18:59.908 --> 19:01.707
And in three minutes,
we're gonna go through there,

19:01.709 --> 19:05.111
and we're gonna get
the safe out like we planned!

19:05.113 --> 19:06.378
Okay?

19:06.380 --> 19:10.783
♪♪

19:10.785 --> 19:12.318
Sorry about that.

19:12.320 --> 19:13.920
I'm trying to entertain
the people and run a business,

19:13.922 --> 19:16.054
got these fools banging
on the walls and stuff.

19:16.056 --> 19:18.324
Gentlemen.
How's it going?

19:18.326 --> 19:20.058
How are you?

19:20.060 --> 19:22.328
Dude, you're awesome.
Oh, thank you.

19:22.330 --> 19:23.862
Guys, this is Marion.

19:23.864 --> 19:25.531
He's the owner of this
fine establishment.

19:25.533 --> 19:32.271
♪♪

19:32.273 --> 19:38.276
♪♪

19:38.278 --> 19:39.612
Shit.

19:39.614 --> 19:42.881
♪♪

19:42.883 --> 19:44.750
This is supposed
to be his office.

19:44.752 --> 19:46.018
This is not supposed
to be here.

19:46.020 --> 19:47.620
Yeah, no shit.

19:47.622 --> 19:49.021
I thought
you scouted this.

19:49.023 --> 19:50.356
I know.
He must not have permitted it.

19:50.358 --> 19:51.958
It wasn't in
the city plans.

19:51.960 --> 20:00.967
♪♪

20:00.969 --> 20:01.834
Hold up.

20:01.836 --> 20:03.302
Craig:
Hold up, my ass, bro.

20:03.304 --> 20:04.903
We're -- We're done.

20:04.905 --> 20:07.239
[ Rapping ]
♪ Better run, run and hide ♪

20:07.241 --> 20:09.908
♪ We comin' down the block,
taking what you got ♪

20:09.910 --> 20:12.110
♪ Better run, run and hide ♪

20:12.112 --> 20:14.913
Get the tools
from J now.

20:14.915 --> 20:16.182
Bro.

20:16.184 --> 20:18.851
Get the tools from J.

20:18.853 --> 20:22.188
Yo, J.
Tools.

20:22.190 --> 20:27.593
♪♪

20:27.595 --> 20:32.999
♪♪

20:33.001 --> 20:34.667
J:
What the hell, man?

20:34.669 --> 20:36.669
The office is outside
of this door.

20:36.671 --> 20:39.271
♪♪

20:39.273 --> 20:40.739
♪ You know the rules ♪

20:40.741 --> 20:43.409
♪ I go to work when
I go berserk, red alert ♪

20:43.411 --> 20:45.477
♪ I'm at my best
when I'm at my worst ♪

20:45.479 --> 20:47.413
♪ So bring it on, I crush
boulders with my fist ♪

20:47.415 --> 20:49.147
How are we gonna get the safe
out the building

20:49.149 --> 20:51.217
without
anyone seeing us?

20:51.219 --> 20:53.952
It's fine. There's a window
in the office.

20:53.954 --> 20:55.954
We can just hoist the safe up
and push it out the window.

20:55.956 --> 20:57.690
There's a window?
Yeah.

20:57.692 --> 20:58.957
A window?
That's part of your plan, too?

20:58.959 --> 21:00.226
Go get the truck
and bring it around.

21:00.228 --> 21:01.694
Don't worry about the tools.
We'll leave 'em.

21:01.696 --> 21:03.095
We're getting
what we came for.

21:03.097 --> 21:05.431
Come on.

21:05.433 --> 21:06.833
Window. Great.

21:06.835 --> 21:09.635
♪ Run and hide ♪

21:09.637 --> 21:16.242
♪♪

21:16.244 --> 21:17.509
Let's find the safe.

21:17.511 --> 21:20.446
[ Cellphone rings ]

21:20.448 --> 21:22.781
Shit.
I gotta get this.

21:22.783 --> 21:24.450
Hey, yo.
Warren, what's up, man?

21:24.452 --> 21:26.385
My money's not good enough
for you?

21:26.387 --> 21:28.654
Oh, but you got people over
there banging on the walls, man.

21:28.656 --> 21:31.457
[ Banging ]

21:31.459 --> 21:33.191
Then who is it, then?

21:33.193 --> 21:35.728
Make sure
no one can get in here.

21:40.869 --> 21:43.269
No, that's all right.

21:43.271 --> 21:45.538
I'll take care of it.

21:45.540 --> 21:47.205
Come on.

21:47.207 --> 21:55.681
♪♪

21:55.683 --> 21:58.084
[ Grunts ]

21:58.086 --> 22:07.626
♪♪

22:07.628 --> 22:09.027
Hey!

22:09.029 --> 22:10.896
Hey!
Open this door!

22:10.898 --> 22:12.698
Open this door!

22:12.700 --> 22:16.568
♪♪

22:16.570 --> 22:18.036
Hey, I see you in there.

22:18.038 --> 22:19.838
When I get in there,
that's your ass, boy!

22:19.840 --> 22:21.373
[ Grunts ]
That's your ass!

22:21.375 --> 22:23.643
All right, the rest of you,
on me. Let's go, let's go.

22:25.446 --> 22:27.747
Hi.
Danielle.

22:30.250 --> 22:31.317
Bitch.

22:31.319 --> 22:32.851
She don't go nowhere.

22:32.853 --> 22:35.387
Got it.
Come on.

22:35.389 --> 22:37.255
[ Engine starts ]

22:37.257 --> 22:41.727
♪♪

22:41.729 --> 22:43.863
Yo, yo. Come on, come on,
come on, come on!

22:44.732 --> 22:46.799
A little more.
Open the window.

22:46.801 --> 22:49.335
[ Banging ]

22:49.337 --> 22:50.536
J: It's stuck.

22:50.538 --> 22:53.271
Just lift it!
[ Grunts ]

22:53.273 --> 23:00.612
♪♪

23:00.614 --> 23:01.814
Let's go.

23:01.816 --> 23:09.621
♪♪

23:09.623 --> 23:10.756
Move!

23:10.758 --> 23:12.891
Shit! Come on!

23:12.893 --> 23:15.561
[ All grunting ]

23:15.563 --> 23:20.032
♪♪

23:20.034 --> 23:20.833
Shit.

23:20.835 --> 23:22.835
Go, go!

23:22.837 --> 23:24.302
Don't touch me.

23:24.304 --> 23:25.571
You better let go of me,
or I'm calling the cops!

23:25.573 --> 23:26.839
You ain't callin' anyone.
Give me the --

23:26.841 --> 23:28.106
Fine, fine!

23:28.108 --> 23:29.375
Come on!

23:29.377 --> 23:32.310
Aah! Aaah!

23:32.312 --> 23:33.445
Aaaah!

23:33.447 --> 23:35.714
Shit! Aah!

23:35.716 --> 23:36.916
Bitch!

23:38.452 --> 23:40.186
Aah!

23:40.188 --> 23:48.927
♪♪

23:48.929 --> 23:50.396
Craig: Get him out!

23:50.398 --> 23:52.798
♪♪

23:52.800 --> 23:55.735
Go, go, go, go!

24:09.917 --> 24:11.450
[ Sighs ]

24:13.320 --> 24:15.654
[ Door slams ]

24:15.656 --> 24:17.590
You know, when we say
we're burned,

24:17.592 --> 24:21.460
we're burned, all right?

24:21.462 --> 24:23.462
We did it.
We have the safe.

24:23.464 --> 24:26.732
J: Yeah.
We almost got busted.

24:26.734 --> 24:29.068
You know, I made the call.
I would've made it again.

24:29.070 --> 24:31.470
Yeah, you know who
you sound like, right?

24:31.472 --> 24:33.206
<i> We</i> make the calls,
all right?

24:33.208 --> 24:36.008
Together, not just you.

24:36.010 --> 24:37.410
God damn it.

24:37.412 --> 24:39.011
Renn is still
not answering.

24:39.013 --> 24:41.146
Well, you know, the plan was
for her to get out on her own,

24:41.148 --> 24:42.347
which she did.

24:42.349 --> 24:43.949
Oh, yeah?
She text you?

24:43.951 --> 24:45.951
Did she let you know
that she's okay?
No.

24:45.953 --> 24:47.753
Well, no, then you don't know
shit then, do you?

24:47.755 --> 24:49.422
Yeah, I know that
she can handle herself.

24:49.424 --> 24:51.490
She's got more balls
than you do.

24:51.492 --> 24:53.692
All right, hey, hey!
You better hope for your sake
that she's all right.

24:53.694 --> 24:55.227
What are you gonna do?
What are you gonna do?
Hey, quit it!
Break it up.

24:55.229 --> 24:57.963
Hey, stop!
Stop. Stop.

24:57.965 --> 24:59.232
You done?

24:59.234 --> 25:02.101
Call Renn again.

25:02.103 --> 25:04.437
God damn it, dude.

25:04.439 --> 25:05.771
What, you got a problem,
too?

25:05.773 --> 25:07.239
No, we just need to hand
over the safe

25:07.241 --> 25:10.375
and get our shit back.

25:10.377 --> 25:12.244
Not yet.

25:12.246 --> 25:13.479
Huh?

25:15.450 --> 25:17.049
Not yet.

25:17.051 --> 25:20.986
♪♪

25:20.988 --> 25:23.188
[ Panting ]

25:23.190 --> 25:29.929
♪♪

25:29.931 --> 25:32.331
[ Laughs ]

25:32.333 --> 25:39.338
♪♪

25:39.340 --> 25:46.546
♪♪

25:50.617 --> 25:53.552
You do all this?

25:53.554 --> 25:55.288
No.

25:55.290 --> 25:56.889
This one's mine.

26:07.302 --> 26:10.503
I'm Cassandra.

26:10.505 --> 26:12.237
Andrew.

26:12.239 --> 26:14.573
That's a nice name.

26:14.575 --> 26:16.642
How'd you find this place,
Andrew?

26:18.980 --> 26:22.447
I don't know.

26:22.449 --> 26:24.049
What about you?

26:24.051 --> 26:25.184
You live here?

26:25.186 --> 26:28.253
No, I got a place
out in Thermal.

26:28.255 --> 26:30.255
You know where that is?

26:30.257 --> 26:31.924
No.
That's okay.

26:31.926 --> 26:34.793
Neither does anybody else.

26:34.795 --> 26:39.932
So, uh...what are you
doing here?

26:39.934 --> 26:44.603
Um, I was going through
a rough patch.

26:44.605 --> 26:47.340
I was driving by,
saw the signs, figured,

26:47.342 --> 26:48.874
"What have I got to lose?"

26:48.876 --> 26:51.944
Well, he said this place
was a church.

26:51.946 --> 26:53.880
That what this
looks like to you?

26:56.417 --> 26:58.351
Looks like it's time.

26:58.353 --> 26:59.818
Time for what?

26:59.820 --> 27:01.621
You're gonna like it.

27:07.162 --> 27:08.961
Thank you.

27:16.637 --> 27:18.004
Here you go.

27:21.776 --> 27:25.178
Nah, drugs
don't work on me.

27:25.180 --> 27:27.713
It's not a drug.

27:27.715 --> 27:29.514
It's a tool.

27:29.516 --> 27:31.651
First step
to finding the truth.

27:33.921 --> 27:35.054
What truth?

27:35.056 --> 27:37.122
That's what you're
looking to find out.

27:37.124 --> 27:39.192
[ Chuckles ]

27:39.194 --> 27:40.993
Come on.
No.

27:43.530 --> 27:45.798
This is our sacrament.

27:45.800 --> 27:49.001
You want to stay,
you -- you drink.

27:49.003 --> 27:52.337
If you don't want to drink,
just...

27:52.339 --> 27:54.407
keep on driving.

27:54.409 --> 27:58.811
♪♪

27:58.813 --> 28:02.681
What have you got to lose?

28:02.683 --> 28:05.084
[ Sighs ]

28:05.086 --> 28:13.358
♪♪

28:13.360 --> 28:21.500
♪♪

28:21.502 --> 28:29.775
♪♪

28:29.777 --> 28:38.317
♪♪

28:38.319 --> 28:46.591
♪♪

28:46.593 --> 28:49.128
[ Sighs ]

28:49.130 --> 28:55.134
♪♪

29:07.949 --> 29:11.617
Jesus!
Is she okay?

29:11.619 --> 29:13.319
She's just scared.

29:15.890 --> 29:17.890
Hey.
What happened?

29:21.095 --> 29:23.428
Where --
How bad is it?

29:23.430 --> 29:24.964
Jake.

29:24.966 --> 29:28.367
Come here, come here.
Both of you, come here.

29:28.369 --> 29:29.434
You're fine.

29:29.436 --> 29:30.836
[ Door closes ]

29:30.838 --> 29:32.271
Stop crying.

29:33.841 --> 29:35.574
What happened?

29:35.576 --> 29:36.641
The man beat him up.

29:36.643 --> 29:39.044
Who? What man?

29:39.046 --> 29:42.581
He punched him and kicked him
and stepped on him...

29:42.583 --> 29:44.583
here.

29:44.585 --> 29:45.918
He said his name.

29:45.920 --> 29:49.388
He said his name?

29:49.390 --> 29:51.891
Max -- Max Cross.

29:53.794 --> 29:55.661
Okay.

29:55.663 --> 29:59.398
You -- You don't tell anyone
about this, okay?

29:59.400 --> 30:01.600
You're gonna be fine.
Everything's gonna be fine.

30:01.602 --> 30:03.736
Don't worry.

30:03.738 --> 30:06.539
Mommy's gonna
take care of this.

30:06.541 --> 30:09.208
Jake?

30:09.210 --> 30:10.676
Jake.

30:10.678 --> 30:19.284
♪♪

30:19.286 --> 30:27.693
♪♪

30:27.695 --> 30:36.301
♪♪

30:36.303 --> 30:37.836
I gotta go.

30:37.838 --> 30:44.577
♪♪

30:44.579 --> 30:51.784
♪♪

30:51.786 --> 30:53.586
[ Exhales deeply ]

30:53.588 --> 31:03.462
♪♪

31:03.464 --> 31:13.538
♪♪

31:13.540 --> 31:16.875
[ Sighs ]
Hey.

31:16.877 --> 31:20.213
You okay?

31:20.215 --> 31:22.181
Hey.

31:24.952 --> 31:26.485
Can you feel it?

31:26.487 --> 31:31.090
♪♪

31:31.092 --> 31:32.792
Hey.

31:33.961 --> 31:35.761
Oh, oh, oh.

31:35.763 --> 31:37.096
Look at me.

31:37.098 --> 31:38.964
What do you see?

31:38.966 --> 31:45.238
♪♪

31:45.240 --> 31:47.506
[ Voice breaking ] I see
somebody I used to know.

31:47.508 --> 31:50.976
[ Laughs ]

31:50.978 --> 31:53.779
I'm sorry.

31:53.781 --> 31:55.514
[ Sniffles ]

31:55.516 --> 31:57.783
She made me do it.

31:57.785 --> 32:02.254
♪<i> As you're walking through</i>
<i> the valley of truth</i> ♪

32:02.256 --> 32:06.592
♪<i> It won't be the end of this</i> ♪

32:06.594 --> 32:07.560
[ Radio turns off ]

32:17.805 --> 32:19.872
[ Door closes ]

32:26.413 --> 32:30.216
Where's Craig...
and your nephew?

32:32.619 --> 32:34.687
They left.

32:34.689 --> 32:37.089
And the package?

32:37.091 --> 32:39.959
Yeah, left with them.

32:39.961 --> 32:41.694
I thought
we had an agreement.

32:41.696 --> 32:43.296
We do.

32:43.298 --> 32:46.098
Just want to make sure
you hold up your end of it.

32:46.100 --> 32:48.634
We always hold up
our end.

32:48.636 --> 32:50.235
Good.

32:50.237 --> 32:51.770
We'll be giving you
a memorandum of understanding

32:51.772 --> 32:55.308
that says you agree to transfer
Smurf's estate back to us.

32:55.310 --> 32:57.610
The safe stays with us
until you sign it.

33:00.515 --> 33:03.248
So much for trust.

33:03.250 --> 33:04.583
You know, Smurf --
she taught us

33:04.585 --> 33:07.452
not to trust
anybody but family.

33:07.454 --> 33:10.189
That's a hard way
to live your life.

33:13.194 --> 33:15.061
Know what I think?

33:16.797 --> 33:21.066
I think your mother did this
because she wanted us to meet.

33:21.068 --> 33:22.467
I think
she wanted you to know

33:22.469 --> 33:24.803
there's someone
you could turn to

33:24.805 --> 33:27.273
if you ever needed help.

33:30.611 --> 33:32.278
Yeah.

33:34.349 --> 33:37.616
Well, it was nice
to meet you.

33:37.618 --> 33:39.952
Hmm.

33:39.954 --> 33:41.587
Nice to meet you, too.

33:43.691 --> 33:45.490
We good?

33:45.492 --> 33:46.825
Yeah.

33:46.827 --> 33:48.627
We're good.

33:48.629 --> 33:58.137
♪♪

34:17.659 --> 34:22.461
[ Door opens, closes ]

34:22.463 --> 34:25.197
Hey.
You're home.

34:25.199 --> 34:26.932
I started without you.
Sorry.

34:26.934 --> 34:29.869
No worries.

34:29.871 --> 34:32.004
You okay?

34:32.006 --> 34:34.807
Yeah. Yeah.

34:37.478 --> 34:39.078
[ Sighs ]

34:39.080 --> 34:42.348
You know, it was supposed to go
a lot smoother than that.

34:42.350 --> 34:43.949
You want to
tell me about it?

34:43.951 --> 34:45.617
[ Sighs ]

34:45.619 --> 34:47.286
Not really.

34:53.761 --> 34:55.962
I had fun.

35:15.783 --> 35:17.450
I get why you do it now.

35:20.254 --> 35:22.922
I do it for the money.

35:22.924 --> 35:26.525
[ Chuckles lightly ]
Yeah.

35:26.527 --> 35:28.127
Sure.

35:37.271 --> 35:39.372
You keeping
the drapes open?

35:42.676 --> 35:44.544
Yeah.
Yeah?

35:44.546 --> 35:46.478
Let 'em watch.

35:46.480 --> 35:48.214
[ Chuckles ]

35:57.891 --> 35:59.892
[ Wind chime chiming softly ]

35:59.894 --> 36:02.027
What is that?

36:02.029 --> 36:03.829
Oh, that thing.

36:03.831 --> 36:05.965
That is a scar.

36:05.967 --> 36:07.967
Where'd you get that?

36:07.969 --> 36:10.770
Oh, yeah.

36:10.772 --> 36:12.171
My brother.
He --

36:12.173 --> 36:16.909
I guess brothers
tend to get rough?

36:16.911 --> 36:19.578
Yeah.

36:19.580 --> 36:22.114
No, it wasn't his fault.

36:22.116 --> 36:24.450
It was my fault.

36:24.452 --> 36:27.587
And nothing was his fault.
It was all my fault.

36:27.589 --> 36:29.322
Where is he?

36:31.725 --> 36:33.392
[ Sighs ]

36:33.394 --> 36:36.728
He's dead.

36:36.730 --> 36:40.132
You.

36:40.134 --> 36:42.134
Get him out of here.

36:42.136 --> 36:43.202
Brian, easy, man.

36:43.204 --> 36:44.670
Why is he looking at me
like that?

36:44.672 --> 36:46.538
Hey, easy, easy.
Everybody's welcome here.

36:46.540 --> 36:48.340
Sit, sit. Come on.
Breathe. Here.

36:48.342 --> 36:50.009
There's something wrong
with him.
No, no, no, no.

36:50.011 --> 36:52.612
Hey, leave him alone.
I don't like this.

36:52.614 --> 36:54.346
He's nothing but darkness.
It's okay. Hey.

36:54.348 --> 36:56.415
Don't listen to him.
He said I'm darkness.

36:56.417 --> 36:58.083
I see you.
Here, take this.

36:58.085 --> 36:59.819
You don't fool me.

36:59.821 --> 37:01.753
Her darkness --
it's inside you.

37:01.755 --> 37:03.155
I can see her.
What?!

37:03.157 --> 37:04.956
Hey, calm down, man.
Sara: Please make him stop.

37:04.958 --> 37:06.358
What did you
just say to me?

37:06.360 --> 37:07.827
Calm down, Brian.
Everything's gonna be okay.

37:07.829 --> 37:09.161
Here you go.
No!

37:09.163 --> 37:11.030
Here. Take that.
He should go, not me.

37:11.032 --> 37:13.165
Sara: I see it.
I-I see it.

37:13.167 --> 37:15.234
Everything's okay.
It's not okay!

37:15.236 --> 37:16.435
Sara: Make him go.

37:16.437 --> 37:17.769
Give me your keys.
[ Grunts ]

37:17.771 --> 37:19.505
Hey. Give me your keys.
Everybody's okay.

37:19.507 --> 37:21.841
She's inside of him?
Get out of here!

37:21.843 --> 37:23.509
Let's go.
Hey, hey.
It's okay.

37:23.511 --> 37:25.110
Let's go. Go. Go.
Devil!

37:25.112 --> 37:26.846
Go straight, straight,
straight!

37:26.848 --> 37:28.580
Straight. Go.

37:28.582 --> 37:32.384
♪♪

37:32.386 --> 37:35.321
[ Police radio chatter ]

37:38.660 --> 37:40.660
[ Door opens ]

37:48.469 --> 37:51.270
Doing some repairs
to the house?

37:51.272 --> 37:53.405
The bowling alley.
Pipe broke.

37:53.407 --> 37:55.341
Sorry to hear that.

37:55.343 --> 37:57.343
Now, I know a good plumber
if you're looking for one.

37:57.345 --> 38:01.613
Not cheap, but you get
what you pay for.

38:01.615 --> 38:04.016
I'm good, thanks.

38:04.018 --> 38:06.151
Hey, uh,
how's your uncle doing?

38:06.153 --> 38:07.419
He's fine.
Okay, good, good.

38:07.421 --> 38:10.222
Glad I could help
with that.

38:10.224 --> 38:13.625
About that. Um...

38:13.627 --> 38:17.229
You're a little short on friends
in the department.

38:17.231 --> 38:20.632
Barker's gone,
retired.

38:20.634 --> 38:24.436
He's an asshole anyway,
if you ask me, but...

38:24.438 --> 38:27.907
like I said,
you get what you pay for.

38:27.909 --> 38:29.308
That was Smurf's deal.

38:29.310 --> 38:31.377
Yeah, sure, I get it.

38:31.379 --> 38:34.846
It's a new era, though,
right?

38:34.848 --> 38:36.582
For you guys, for us.

38:39.987 --> 38:42.988
Anyway, I'll let you
get back to work.

38:42.990 --> 38:51.463
♪♪

38:51.465 --> 38:52.999
Wait.

38:55.603 --> 38:58.437
Is there a file on Smurf?
On my family?

39:02.276 --> 39:04.076
I want to see it.

39:04.078 --> 39:14.086
♪♪

39:14.088 --> 39:15.821
[ Engine starts ]

39:15.823 --> 39:23.496
♪♪

39:28.502 --> 39:30.770
If you would've asked around
about this guy two weeks ago

39:30.772 --> 39:34.706
instead of two hours ago,
we wouldn't have this problem.

39:34.708 --> 39:37.576
Everybody's got a boss,
Janine.

39:37.578 --> 39:39.979
It's about time
you figured out who yours is.

39:39.981 --> 39:41.447
Wait here.
What?

39:41.449 --> 39:43.315
No, this is about
all of us.

39:43.317 --> 39:45.251
He didn't come
to your house.

39:50.124 --> 39:51.523
Shit.

39:51.525 --> 39:56.261
♪ There's no sign
of the morning coming ♪

39:56.263 --> 39:58.197
♪ You've been left
on your own ♪

39:58.199 --> 40:00.700
♪ Like a rainbow in the dark ♪

40:02.336 --> 40:03.936
♪ Just a rainbow in the dark ♪

40:03.938 --> 40:05.270
Is Max around?

40:05.272 --> 40:06.672
That way.

40:06.674 --> 40:08.273
♪ Yeah ♪

40:08.275 --> 40:16.816
♪♪

40:16.818 --> 40:25.157
♪♪

40:25.159 --> 40:33.165
♪♪

40:33.167 --> 40:36.235
I heard you might
be able to...

40:36.237 --> 40:38.570
get me something
for this.

40:38.572 --> 40:44.109
♪♪

40:44.111 --> 40:49.715
♪♪

40:49.717 --> 40:53.185
[ Sighs ]

40:53.187 --> 40:55.787
Your name
anywhere near it?

40:55.789 --> 40:57.456
Nope.

41:00.728 --> 41:05.264
Ah, you got some set of balls,
don't you?

41:05.266 --> 41:08.000
I am not the kind of guy

41:08.002 --> 41:13.339
who takes a hammer away
from a carpenter.

41:13.341 --> 41:15.107
However...

41:18.212 --> 41:22.414
...this is not
an open town.

41:22.416 --> 41:27.887
So you're gonna kick me
30% of your take.

41:27.889 --> 41:32.024
And you're gonna tell me
what you're taking

41:32.026 --> 41:37.864
if you're taking it between
Pendleton and National City.

41:39.967 --> 41:41.767
And I'm not asking.

41:41.769 --> 41:43.436
So you don't like it...

41:45.573 --> 41:47.373
...you can shoot me.

41:52.514 --> 41:54.580
Deal.

41:54.582 --> 41:56.315
And I'm gonna need
2 grand right now

41:56.317 --> 41:58.818
for all the shit
you already pulled.

42:01.723 --> 42:03.422
No.

42:05.193 --> 42:08.860
I think we're even.

42:08.862 --> 42:10.630
There is one more thing.

42:13.334 --> 42:14.600
Yeah?

42:14.602 --> 42:20.139
♪♪

42:20.141 --> 42:23.409
You ever come near my kids
again...

42:26.680 --> 42:28.480
...I'll kill you.

42:28.482 --> 42:37.757
♪♪

42:43.497 --> 42:45.297
Where are we?

42:45.299 --> 42:47.166
I don't know.

42:47.168 --> 42:49.402
But I can't keep driving.

42:50.371 --> 42:52.304
Jesus Christ.

42:52.306 --> 42:53.906
That's so beautiful.

42:53.908 --> 42:56.442
We shouldn't stay here.

42:56.444 --> 42:58.878
Why not?

43:01.915 --> 43:04.250
[ Laughing ]

43:07.254 --> 43:08.720
What?

43:08.722 --> 43:10.255
You.

43:10.257 --> 43:12.191
Looking at the road.

43:12.193 --> 43:14.760
[ Laughs ]

43:16.530 --> 43:19.131
It's moving.

43:19.133 --> 43:20.332
Look.

43:20.334 --> 43:21.933
These lines
shouldn't be moving.

43:21.935 --> 43:23.736
[ Laughs ]

43:29.143 --> 43:30.876
[ Sighs ]

43:30.878 --> 43:34.079
That kid Brian
was scared of you.

43:34.081 --> 43:36.349
A lot of people are.

43:38.019 --> 43:40.586
Should I be?

43:44.358 --> 43:47.959
♪♪

43:47.961 --> 43:49.495
No.

43:51.833 --> 43:53.965
Good.

43:53.967 --> 44:02.441
♪♪

44:02.443 --> 44:04.510
Hey,
where you going?

44:04.512 --> 44:07.580
Cassandra: I don't know.
Over there.

44:09.116 --> 44:11.116
Are you coming?

44:11.118 --> 44:14.320
♪♪

44:14.322 --> 44:16.722
[ Horn honks ]

44:18.993 --> 44:21.927
[ Laughing ]

44:21.929 --> 44:28.800
♪♪

44:28.802 --> 44:31.737
♪ Who's gonna wear your crown? ♪

44:31.739 --> 44:33.072
♪ No one ♪

44:33.074 --> 44:38.410
♪ The queens of the underground
or no one ♪

44:38.412 --> 44:42.814
♪ The sirens will never sing ♪

44:42.816 --> 44:45.685
♪ Just silence in everything ♪

44:45.687 --> 44:49.889
♪ For no one at all ♪

44:49.891 --> 44:55.494
♪♪

44:55.496 --> 44:58.764
♪ Who's on the telephone? ♪

44:58.766 --> 45:00.432
♪ Why, no one ♪

45:00.434 --> 45:03.703
♪ Babel or Babylon ♪

45:03.705 --> 45:04.904
♪ Or no one ♪

45:04.906 --> 45:08.374
♪ Dressed up in Halloween ♪

45:08.376 --> 45:09.841
♪ For no one ♪

45:09.843 --> 45:12.844
♪ Where nobody ever screams ♪

45:12.846 --> 45:16.916
♪ For no one at all ♪

45:16.918 --> 45:22.121
♪♪

45:22.123 --> 45:27.192
♪♪

45:27.194 --> 45:33.065
♪ And who's gonna
cut you do-o-o-wn? ♪

45:33.067 --> 45:36.602
♪ Why, no one ♪

45:36.604 --> 45:42.474
♪ And get your feet
on the gro-o-o-und ♪

45:42.476 --> 45:46.412
♪ Why, no one at all ♪

45:46.414 --> 45:52.017
♪♪

45:52.019 --> 45:57.957
♪ Why, no one at all ♪

46:00.962 --> 46:10.102
♪♪

